  "text": "HLA-G has unique immunomodulatory properties through its ability to inhibit NK cell-mediated cytotoxicity [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . We therefore examined the ability of US10 to interfere with HLA-Gmediated inhibition of NK cytotoxicity. In previous studies, killing of the class I-negative human B cell line 721.221 by peripheral NK cells is inhibited by the expression of HLA-G [CITATION_4] Ponte et al., 1999; [CITATION_5] . Peripheral NK (pNK) cells were coincubated with 721.221, 721.221/HLA-G, or 721.221/HLA-G that",
